<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id12209a00-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s725"><num value="725">§ 725.</num><heading> Statement of appropriations; “usual number”</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Of the statements of appropriations required to be prepared by <ref href="/us/usc/t2/s105">section 105 of Title 2</ref>,<ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002001">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002001"><num>1</num> So in original. See References in Text note below.</note> there shall be printed, after the close of each regular session of Congress, the usual number of copies.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id12209a01-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1252">82 Stat. 1252</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id12209a02-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id12209a03-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 153 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-03-02/ch189/s1">Mar. 2, 1895, ch. 189, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/958">28 Stat. 958</ref>).</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id12209a04-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
